import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='region', y='income', data=data)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.legend(title='Region', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('region').agg({'income': 'mean', 'health': 'mean'}).reset_index()
    data_melted = data_grouped.melt(id_vars='region', var_name='metric', value_name='value')

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='region', y='value', hue='metric', data=data_melted)
    plt.title('What is the average income and health of each region?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Metric')
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
